I mean, Cloud Sonnet model has been really good, but the O3 mini could be really good as well.

00:54:28.280 --> 00:54:34.919
Ah, great. Thank you. And a question from Veronica. Is there a remote possibility that

00:54:34.919 --> 00:54:40.919
in the future, these LLMs models cannot be improved? Because there won't be an example

00:54:40.919 --> 00:54:45.560
out in the web to learn new things from just because everyone used the LLM models

00:54:45.560 --> 00:54:49.000
to solve their issues and not sharing the knowledge anymore.

00:54:50.280 --> 00:54:55.560
You know, I am not, you know, I'm not like a deep expert in that side of things.

00:54:56.760 --> 00:55:00.120
I've heard that that's, you know, that kind of thing is possible. Although some of these

00:55:00.120 --> 00:55:04.199
models, they do keep, they are getting better, even though the models aren't getting larger.

00:55:04.199 --> 00:55:08.520
And there's not like a whole lot more training data that's coming into existence now. So,

00:55:08.520 --> 00:55:14.360
part of it is like better training techniques, maybe better architectures. But yeah, are they

00:55:14.360 --> 00:55:19.959
going to hit a limit? Maybe. Maybe they'll have to resort to other techniques like having these

00:55:19.959 --> 00:55:26.199
models, try things, like actually try writing code and then running it and then doing some

00:55:26.199 --> 00:55:32.520
reinforcement learning the results that way. So, yeah. But again, I'm not an expert on it.

00:55:32.520 --> 00:55:38.199
That's just sort of, you know, my thoughts. Personally, I feel that there will always be

00:55:38.199 --> 00:55:45.639
some just people who like doing such stuff and sharing it, you know. So, I think there's always

00:55:45.639 --> 00:55:53.000
something coming. I hope so, yeah. Question from Josh. What is currently being done to alleviate

00:55:53.000 --> 00:56:00.040
some of the current limitation of Shiny Assistant? Well, so there's the Shiny Assistant web version

00:56:00.040 --> 00:56:07.239
and then there's Shiny Assistant for VS Code. So, there's those limitations that I listed.

00:56:08.040 --> 00:56:14.280
And the biggest one is, I think, not being able to, for the VS Code version, not being able to,

00:56:15.959 --> 00:56:21.320
not being as good at writing Shiny code as I would like. As you saw in the demo, which was

00:56:21.320 --> 00:56:25.800
actually, I do have to say that was actually, they had many more errors than I expected from

00:56:25.800 --> 00:56:30.919
my practice runs of this talk. But that is also, it also shows like, you know, here's how you have

00:56:30.919 --> 00:56:34.760
to work with these things. Like, they're going to make mistakes and you're still going to bring

00:56:34.760 --> 00:56:42.439
your brain there. So, I mean, so we're, you know, we are working on improving the system prompts for

00:56:42.439 --> 00:56:49.000
them and putting more information and not just more information, but like efficiently showing them

00:56:49.719 --> 00:56:53.080
with the right way to do things. So, we're not just filling up the system prompt with junk.

00:56:53.879 --> 00:56:59.320
And that is a long process and, you know, we're going to keep working on that. But again,

00:56:59.320 --> 00:57:05.399
then a new LLM model comes out and they behave differently and you sort of have to redo a lot

00:57:05.399 --> 00:57:13.560
of your work again. Absolutely. Question from Tyrone, I guess it's related to demo. Is this

